Based on the implementation of `set_pflash_bsa_mask` in `src/llama-context.cpp` provided in the text:

```cpp
void llama_context::set_pflash_bsa_mask(const int32_t * block_indices, int32_t n_selected) {
    if (!bsa_block_mask || !bsa_block_mask->data || n_selected <= 0 || n_selected > bsa_block_mask->ne[0]) {
        return;
    }

    cparams.bsa_n_selected = n_selected;
    ggml_backend_tensor_set(bsa_block_mask, block_indices, 0,
                            (size_t)n_selected * sizeof(int32_t));
}
```

The two operations performed after the null/bounds check are:

1.  It updates the field **`bsa_n_selected`** in the `llama_cparams` struct (`cparams`).
2.  It calls the ggml function **`ggml_backend_tensor_set`** to transfer the data.
